  <text xml:base="urn:cts:croala:and02.croala702300.croala-lat1:" xml:lang="lat" type="poesis">
      <body xml:lang="lat">
         <div met="hendecasyllabus">
            <head n="head">Tranquillus Parthenius Andronicus Dalmata lectori verum describit philosophum.</head>



            <l n="l1">Hic est maximus ille quem requiris,</l>
            <l n="l2">Nulli par hominum, minus secundus,</l>
            <l n="l3">Nunquam sollicitus, dolore nullo.</l>
            <l n="l4">Quem nec vanus amor metusve rodit:</l>
            <l n="l5">Ignarusque animi furoris: atqui</l>
            <l n="l6">Nec vitae cupidus, sibi nec ipsi</l>
            <l n="l7">Indulgens nimium: sed usque constans.</l>
            <l n="l8">Quem nec frigora, nec gelu, nec aestus,</l>
            <l n="l9">Imbres nec madidi, niuesque dirae,</l>
            <l n="l10">Ventorum aut rabies trucisque saeua</l>
            <l n="l11">Non fati series mouere possunt:</l>
            <l n="l12">Quin semper putet esse se beatum,</l>
            <l n="l13">Fortunae dominus, suique rector.</l>
            <l n="l14">Hunc si partibus assequi licebit</l>
            <l n="l15">Cunctis: Quis neget Herculem, Iouemque</l>
            <l n="l16">Caessuros animo tuo decenti?</l>
         </div>    
      </body>
